{"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"PIDFile","kind":"identifier"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Each running VM writes a PID file at","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"~\/.spooktacular\/vms\/<name>.vm\/pid"},{"text":". The file contains the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"process ID of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook start"},{"text":" process that owns the VM.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Other commands (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"stop"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"list"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ip"},{"text":") read the PID file to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"determine whether a VM is running and to signal the process.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"PID File Lifecycle","level":2,"anchor":"PID-File-Lifecycle","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"spook start","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" writes the PID file before booting the VM.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook stop"},{"type":"text","text":" reads the PID file and sends SIGTERM."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook start"},{"text":" installs a SIGTERM handler that gracefully","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"stops the VM, removes the PID file, and exits.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If the process crashes, the PID file becomes stale.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isProcessAlive(_:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" detects stale PID files by checking","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"whether the recorded process is still running.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Thread-Safety","text":"Thread Safety"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All methods are static and operate on the file system. They"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are safe to call from any thread. The PID file is a plain"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"text file containing a single integer, so reads and writes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are effectively atomic at the file-system level."}]}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"title":"PIDFile","externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit7PIDFileO","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"PIDFile","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"symbolKind":"enum","roleHeading":"Enumeration","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"PIDFile","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Manages PID files for tracking running virtual machines.","type":"text"}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Type Properties","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/fileName"],"anchor":"Type-Properties"},{"title":"Type Methods","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isProcessAlive(_:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isRunning(bundleURL:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/read(from:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/remove(from:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/do